1
00:00:00,834 --> 00:00:02,002
(MOUSE SQUEAKS)

2
00:00:02,127 --> 00:00:03,504
(PENGUINS CHIRP)

3
00:00:05,464 --> 00:00:06,882
(ALL CHEERING)

4
00:00:09,510 --> 00:00:10,511
(SCREECHES)

5
00:00:10,552 --> 00:00:11,553
(QUACKS)

6
00:00:12,804 --> 00:00:13,931
Adventure Time

7
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,390
Come on, grab your friends

8
00:00:15,432 --> 00:00:18,018
We'll go to very distant lands

9
00:00:18,101 --> 00:00:20,354
With Jake the dog
and Finn the human

10
00:00:20,395 --> 00:00:22,272
The fun will never end

11
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:24,149
It's Adventure Time

12
00:00:31,532 --> 00:00:33,659
So, then Melissa's like,
"What do you think of him?"

13
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,953
And I'm all, "Well, he's no
ray of sunshine or whatever."

14
00:00:36,078 --> 00:00:37,079
(JAKE WHOOPING)

15
00:00:37,162 --> 00:00:39,790
You know these people you just
get, like, neggy vibes from?

16
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:41,833
Yeah, like bad jubies or something.

17
00:00:41,959 --> 00:00:42,960
Totally.

18
00:00:43,085 --> 00:00:47,297
They just put everyone in a wack mood
with their bad jubies!

19
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:49,967
(LAUGHTER)

20
00:00:50,092 --> 00:00:51,218
Whoops.

21
00:00:51,468 --> 00:00:53,303
Oh, man. My body feels weird.

22
00:00:53,345 --> 00:00:57,349
Uh, dude, that's 'cause you just got
glide-sliced by the ice duo. (LAUGHS)

23
00:00:57,474 --> 00:00:59,351
Yeah, my body feels weird, too.

24
00:00:59,434 --> 00:01:01,436
- Here, Finn, feel this.
- BEEMO: Ah!

25
00:01:01,478 --> 00:01:02,729
- (ALARM BLARES)
- Whoa!

26
00:01:02,813 --> 00:01:05,315
Too much electricity to the noggin, bro.

27
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:07,401
- He'll be fine.
- (BEEPING) Oh!

28
00:01:07,651 --> 00:01:09,444
- JAKE: See? Fine.
- (LAUGHS)

29
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:11,071
That was...
(DISTORTED) weird.

30
00:01:11,196 --> 00:01:13,782
MAN: This is a storm alert
from the automated weather service

31
00:01:13,824 --> 00:01:16,285
in effect for the grasslands
and all surrounding areas.

32
00:01:16,326 --> 00:01:18,954
Residents must evacuate
or seek shelter immediately.

33
00:01:19,204 --> 00:01:20,455
Wait, what?

34
00:01:20,706 --> 00:01:22,958
- (CHEERFUL MUSIC PLAYS)
- MAN: And now your local forecast.

35
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:24,418
(MAN READING)

36
00:01:28,964 --> 00:01:30,465
How long's this gonna last, man?

37
00:01:32,342 --> 00:01:33,677
A whole week?

38
00:01:33,844 --> 00:01:35,304
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

39
00:01:35,679 --> 00:01:37,723
- (GLITCHES)
- (NORMAL VOICE) What do we do?

40
00:01:38,056 --> 00:01:39,683
My dudes, check it.

41
00:01:39,725 --> 00:01:41,602
Super-sweet underground bunker time!

42
00:01:41,685 --> 00:01:43,562
But we got to build this thing fast.

43
00:01:43,604 --> 00:01:45,105
I'll collect building materials.

44
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:46,982
Beemo, you stock up on water.

45
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:48,734
LSP, you gather food.

46
00:01:48,984 --> 00:01:51,194
And Jake, you... Where'd he go?

47
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:57,492
Jake! (SIGHS) Hey, man.
Whatcha doing up here?

48
00:01:57,576 --> 00:01:59,620
We need help building
the underground thingamajiggy.

49
00:01:59,828 --> 00:02:02,581
I think I just need a little time up here
for a minute, dude.

50
00:02:02,706 --> 00:02:04,458
What is it, man, nervous poots?

51
00:02:04,499 --> 00:02:06,877
Uh... Naw. Naw, man, nothing like that.

52
00:02:06,877 --> 00:02:10,297
It's cool, man. Just come down soon.
We're gonna need your help.

53
00:02:13,175 --> 00:02:14,551
Hmm...

54
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:16,553
(FARTS)

55
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:20,891
(GRUNTS)

56
00:02:20,932 --> 00:02:25,020
Aw, man! This is gonna take me all day.
Where you getting all that food, LSP?

57
00:02:25,062 --> 00:02:26,521
I took it from that guy's house.

58
00:02:27,314 --> 00:02:29,566
- What?
- Chill, homie. Nobody's there.

59
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:31,526
It's, like, abandoned or something.

60
00:02:31,568 --> 00:02:34,071
Yeah? Oh-kay...

61
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:37,407
(HUMMING)

62
00:02:37,574 --> 00:02:40,327
Beemo, what is the deal with Jake?

63
00:02:40,410 --> 00:02:42,704
Oh, he's down by the river.

64
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:44,706
But shouldn't he be helping us?

65
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:47,084
My arms are already, like, super-tired

66
00:02:47,209 --> 00:02:49,086
from carrying all those bags of chips.

67
00:02:49,086 --> 00:02:50,587
This isn't fair!

68
00:02:50,712 --> 00:02:52,589
- (WHISTLING)
- Oh, okay.

69
00:02:52,714 --> 00:02:54,841
The Beemo will talk to him.

70
00:02:54,925 --> 00:02:56,051
Hmph!

71
00:02:56,176 --> 00:02:58,220
(SINGSONG) Water bot!

72
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:00,472
I am the water bot!

73
00:03:00,555 --> 00:03:03,058
I have a water body!

74
00:03:03,308 --> 00:03:06,228
- (ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)
- Oops! (GIGGLES)

75
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:09,731
I will never know the pleasures
of skinny-dipping.

76
00:03:10,482 --> 00:03:11,858
Jake!

77
00:03:13,985 --> 00:03:15,237
Hey, there, buddy.

78
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,613
- (CHIRPING)
- BEEMO: Jake!

79
00:03:16,738 --> 00:03:18,365
Jake! There you are!

80
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:20,242
The storm is getting closer.

81
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:22,369
Look! (BEEPING)

82
00:03:22,452 --> 00:03:24,121
We need your help.

83
00:03:24,371 --> 00:03:27,874
Well... (SIGHS) The thing is,
I've been working on this thing,

84
00:03:27,999 --> 00:03:30,877
and I've been collecting, like, lots of stuff.

85
00:03:31,002 --> 00:03:33,505
Um, I just can't really show anybody yet.

86
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:35,757
But trust me, man, it'll be great, I promise.

87
00:03:36,383 --> 00:03:39,261
But... But Jake, I don't see anything here.

88
00:03:39,386 --> 00:03:41,513
You're thinking too much with those eyeballs,

89
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:43,598
not enough with your mind hole...

90
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:46,351
Or whatever computer thingy
you got up in there.

91
00:03:46,393 --> 00:03:48,895
I'll catch ya later, man! Don't worry.

92
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:52,149
(ALARM BEEPING)

93
00:03:57,612 --> 00:03:58,780
(RIBBITS)

94
00:04:18,008 --> 00:04:19,134
Nailed it.

95
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:20,635
Lousy Finn and cans...

96
00:04:20,719 --> 00:04:23,388
Jake... Making me put
these cans up on the shelf...

97
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:24,848
(GRUNTING)

98
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:27,601
- (CLATTERING)
- (SHOUTING) That's it!

99
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:29,895
Is Jake staying in this bunker or what?

100
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:32,230
I mean, of course. It's for everyone.

101
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:35,484
But he hasn't lumping done anything!

102
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:37,903
Oh, but he said he was
working on something.

103
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:41,156
Get real, Beemo!
That fool needs to get schooled.

104
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:44,284
(GRUMBLING)

105
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:46,661
Oh, heck no! Unh-uh!

106
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:49,915
Excuse mel

107
00:04:49,998 --> 00:04:53,752
Are you not aware that we are all working
our steamy butts off down there

108
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:56,671
so we don't get wiped out
by this crazy sky nightmare?

109
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:58,673
Whoa, whoa. Hold up.

110
00:04:58,757 --> 00:05:00,675
I'm working on something up here. It...

111
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:03,261
I see nothing! You're working on nothing!

112
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:08,809
Look, LSP, can we just take a moment
to appreciate this moment?

113
00:05:08,934 --> 00:05:11,144
Look at this crazy sweet sunset.

114
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:13,939
When's the next time
you're gonna see a sunset like this?

115
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:15,816
Or any sunset, really?

116
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:18,443
Who knows how long we'll be down there?

117
00:05:18,527 --> 00:05:19,694
(EAGLE SCREECHES)

118
00:05:20,278 --> 00:05:22,030
(SCREAMING)

119
00:05:22,405 --> 00:05:25,784
I obviously love sunsets and cute animals,
but we don't have time for this right now!

120
00:05:25,826 --> 00:05:27,327
- But I...
- You know what?

121
00:05:27,410 --> 00:05:30,205
(INHALES SHARPLY)
I just can't with you right now.

122
00:05:31,581 --> 00:05:33,708
- Can't what?
- (WHOOSHES)

123
00:05:33,959 --> 00:05:35,210
(SCREECHES)

124
00:05:37,921 --> 00:05:39,047
(THUNDER CRASHES)

125
00:05:39,089 --> 00:05:40,841
Jake! He hates lightning.

126
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:44,219
- (CHUCKLES)
- Ah, Jake, you're back.

127
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:46,721
- Yeah. Heh.
- So, what'd you bring, man?

128
00:05:46,805 --> 00:05:48,807
Heard you were working on something big.

129
00:05:48,974 --> 00:05:52,227
Well, I've been jotting some
stuff down in my notebook.

130
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:54,354
Oh, cool. Like survival tips and junk?

131
00:05:54,437 --> 00:05:57,941
No, not really. It's more like, um...

132
00:05:58,066 --> 00:05:59,359
It's a surprise.

133
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:01,862
Oh. So, you didn't bring anything.

134
00:06:01,987 --> 00:06:03,864
- (THUNDER RUMBLES, CRASHES)
- Oh, snap!

135
00:06:03,947 --> 00:06:05,448
Got to seal the door!

136
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:08,994
- Beemo, light this baby up.
- Ooh!

137
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:10,495
- (ELECTRICITY HUMS)
- Ooh!

138
00:06:10,579 --> 00:06:12,122
Okay. All boarded up.

139
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:13,707
Now we wait.

140
00:06:13,748 --> 00:06:15,959
We just wait? That's it?

141
00:06:16,001 --> 00:06:18,712
Can we at least play a game or something?
I'm already bored.

142
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:19,963
Sure. What game?

143
00:06:20,005 --> 00:06:21,131
Spin the Bottle.

144
00:06:21,131 --> 00:06:23,383
- Yee!
- Sorry, LSP. Ain't got no bottles.

145
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:25,635
(GULPING)

146
00:06:25,719 --> 00:06:27,387
Yes, we do. (BELCHES)

147
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:29,890
Yo, what gives? We got to ration that water!

148
00:06:29,973 --> 00:06:31,141
I have needs, Finn!

149
00:06:31,141 --> 00:06:32,893
- (BOTTLE SHATTERS)
- Just sit there, then.

150
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:35,103
I'll be texting Brad
until you change your min...

151
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:38,523
(CELL PHONE CLATTERS)

152
00:06:40,609 --> 00:06:43,653
And that's why you should
never rely on technology.

153
00:06:43,737 --> 00:06:45,155
No offense, Beemo.

154
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:47,908
- Is she okay?
- Yeah, I think she's already asleep.

155
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:51,161
(SNORING)

156
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:07,761
(YAWNS) Hey, you guys hungry?

157
00:07:07,886 --> 00:07:09,888
- JAKE: Mmm-hmm.
- Hungry...

158
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:11,932
Yo, LSP, throw me some chips.

159
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:14,434
(MUNCHING, MUFFLED) No more chips.

160
00:07:14,643 --> 00:07:16,186
How about some of them bean-beans?

161
00:07:16,311 --> 00:07:18,271
No. No more.

162
00:07:18,313 --> 00:07:22,067
Looks like we've got a can of,
like, beet... Something.

163
00:07:22,192 --> 00:07:24,277
Wait, what? Is that all that's left?

164
00:07:24,319 --> 00:07:25,445
I was hungies!

165
00:07:25,695 --> 00:07:28,573
You ate all the food? I can't believe you!

166
00:07:28,573 --> 00:07:31,034
Whatever, Finn. I'm not here to make friends.

167
00:07:31,076 --> 00:07:32,661
- (WIND HOWLING)
- I'm here to not die.

168
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:33,787
- (THUD)
- (GROANS)

169
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:35,664
(ALL GASP)

170
00:07:35,914 --> 00:07:37,165
Finn, the door!

171
00:07:37,207 --> 00:07:39,584
You were supposed to secure the door!

172
00:07:39,668 --> 00:07:40,669
Beemo, you saw me do it!

173
00:07:40,710 --> 00:07:42,587
That wood must be bunk or something.

174
00:07:42,712 --> 00:07:44,714
Yeah, I think this food's bunk, too.

175
00:07:44,798 --> 00:07:46,716
It expires in...

176
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,093
Twenty-nine years ago.

177
00:07:48,176 --> 00:07:50,095
Oh, glob! (SCREAMS)

178
00:07:50,178 --> 00:07:52,722
I knew raiding that house was a bad idea.

179
00:07:52,722 --> 00:07:55,058
Well, maybe... Maybe I could've
built something better

180
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:58,103
if I had some help from, oh,
I don't know, my best friend!

181
00:07:58,353 --> 00:07:59,854
- (SCREAMING)
- (ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

182
00:08:00,105 --> 00:08:01,606
No!

183
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:03,108
- (THUNDER CRASHES)
- JAKE: Beemo!

184
00:08:03,108 --> 00:08:04,234
(LSP GRUMBLING)

185
00:08:04,609 --> 00:08:05,819
(BEEPS)

186
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:07,112
What'd I miss?

187
00:08:07,195 --> 00:08:08,613
Why is it dark now?

188
00:08:10,365 --> 00:08:12,450
Yeah, I broke it. Whatever.

189
00:08:12,575 --> 00:08:16,079
Guys, I think this storm is more than just
some scary clouds and weather junk.

190
00:08:16,121 --> 00:08:19,082
We've been treating each other like
ding-dongs since we've been down here.

191
00:08:19,124 --> 00:08:21,626
Duh! This bunker is the worst!

192
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:25,630
Nah, nah. I think this storm's carrying
some major negative energy or something.

193
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,090
Bad jubies.

194
00:08:27,132 --> 00:08:30,260
It's making us all go nanners!
I think I can help, though.

195
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:32,095
Let me show you what I've been working on.

196
00:08:32,262 --> 00:08:33,513
Ahem.

197
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:35,265
(TAKES DEEP BREATH)

198
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:37,392
(IMITATES BIRD CHIRPING)

199
00:08:43,314 --> 00:08:46,192
(IMITATES STREAM FLOWING,
FROG CROAKING)

200
00:08:46,276 --> 00:08:47,569
(INHALES DEEPLY)

201
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:49,821
(IMITATES BIRDS CHIRPING)

202
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:52,532
It is so beautiful!

203
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:55,952
(CHIRPING, CROAKING CONTINUE)

204
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:00,832
(CLEARS THROAT, GASPS)

205
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:03,084
(WHISTLING, CROAKING RHYTHMICALLY)

206
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:06,421
(BEATBOXING)

207
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:09,841
(ALARM BLARES)

208
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:13,720
Holy tornado twins!

209
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:16,056
(THUNDER CRASHES)

210
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:17,974
Peek-a-boo! I'mma hurt you!

211
00:09:18,099 --> 00:09:19,434
- No!
- Don't hurt us!

212
00:09:19,476 --> 00:09:22,228
But I only feel good about myself
when I knock other people down!

213
00:09:22,312 --> 00:09:23,354
(LAUGHS EVILLY)

214
00:09:23,438 --> 00:09:24,481
I told you, man,

215
00:09:24,606 --> 00:09:26,691
this storm's got an attitude problem!

216
00:09:26,733 --> 00:09:29,194
Jake, you gotta help us
get back to our happy place.

217
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:31,571
The only way to fight bad jubies
is with good jubies!

218
00:09:31,613 --> 00:09:33,740
(BEATBOXING, CHIRPING, CROAKING)

219
00:09:33,823 --> 00:09:35,492
- (THUNDER CRASHES)
- (SHRIEKS)

220
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:37,619
Finn, I can't keep this up solo!

221
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:39,621
But we can't make all those sounds!

222
00:09:39,704 --> 00:09:41,247
No time to be self-conscious, man!

223
00:09:41,372 --> 00:09:43,625
(ECHOING) Get on this beat! (BEATBOXING)

224
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,710
Swish! Swish! (BEATBOXING)

225
00:09:45,752 --> 00:09:47,212
- Swish! Swish!
- (CHIRPING)

226
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:49,756
Caw! Ca-caw! Whoal!

227
00:09:49,881 --> 00:09:51,257
Tweet! Tweet! Tweet!

228
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:52,383
What are those noises?

229
00:09:52,467 --> 00:09:54,135
The sound of good vibes!

230
00:09:54,219 --> 00:09:56,096
Yeah, the dope beats of life!

231
00:09:56,221 --> 00:09:59,015
- (RAIN POURING)
- It makes me feel some type of way.

232
00:09:59,224 --> 00:10:02,602
How about you pause that stormin' for a sec
so you can hear the rest of it?

233
00:10:02,644 --> 00:10:03,895
(RAIN, THUNDER STOP)

234
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,271
(IMITATES BIRDS CHIRPING)

235
00:10:05,396 --> 00:10:07,148
Wait. Wait, wait. That one. What's that one?

236
00:10:07,232 --> 00:10:09,275
(CAWING)

237
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:11,528
No, no, no. That "tweet-tweet" one.

238
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,863
- (IMITATES BIRDS CHIRPING)
- Yes! Ohh...

239
00:10:13,905 --> 00:10:17,408
I haven't heard that sound
since I was a baby breeze.

240
00:10:17,534 --> 00:10:20,912
What? You forgot what a bird sounds like?
No wonder you're depressed!

241
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:23,373
You know, you should really stop
and slow down more often.

242
00:10:23,414 --> 00:10:26,167
Yeah. You get to hear life happening.
Makes you feel good.

243
00:10:26,251 --> 00:10:28,002
(INHALES DEEPLY)

244
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:29,671
(DEEP SIGH)

245
00:10:29,921 --> 00:10:32,298
You're right!
I've been a freaky storm for so long

246
00:10:32,423 --> 00:10:34,926
that I forgot it's okay
to be a breeze sometimes.

247
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:36,511
If you'll excuse me,

248
00:10:36,553 --> 00:10:39,514
I'm going to explore
the rest of this beautiful day.

249
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:42,267
Wait! Here, man. Take my notebook.

250
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:44,310
It's got the sheet music to my jam.

251
00:10:44,394 --> 00:10:46,563
Really? You would do that?

252
00:10:46,688 --> 00:10:47,939
Yeah, just take it.

253
00:10:47,939 --> 00:10:49,315
(WIND HOWLING)

254
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:52,068
Thank you so much, stretchy dog.

255
00:10:52,152 --> 00:10:56,447
This is one of the nicest things
anyone's ever done for me.

256
00:10:56,573 --> 00:10:57,574
Outey!

257
00:11:00,285 --> 00:11:01,828
Yes! The sun!

258
00:11:01,911 --> 00:11:03,037
Hoo-hoo!

259
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:05,540
I am sorry we doubted you, Jake.

260
00:11:05,582 --> 00:11:06,833
Ditto.

261
00:11:06,958 --> 00:11:08,459
Proud of you, man.

262
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:13,339
- (EAGLE SCREECHES)
- (SCREAMS)

263
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:18,178
Come along with me

264
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:22,557
And the butterflies and bees

265
00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:28,354
This party is so crazy!

